<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-05-03T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-05-03T10:00:00-05:00" n="229" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d229">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">814.51/286: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-05-03T11:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">May 3,
                                            1919, 11 a.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>Your April 23, 5 p.m.</p>
                            <p>Additional issue of sixty millions paper will make ultimate reform of
                                currency much more difficult and should be prevented if possible. It
                                is left to your discretion to make such representations to President
                                Estrada as you think most likely to dissuade him from signing bill
                                in question, referring to interest which United States feels and has
                                shown in establishing currency of Guatemala on a gold basis.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>